Farmer dashboard AMS findings panel to be displayed to all those with Red findings Round 1
Is not shown for anyone with no findings
Pre-submit, those with Red findings see findings, count and Respond to findings button
For partnerships - only PP can see Respond to findings

(note - change to message from last year - new date)

 

Post submit scenarios - (test only) in Jira BISSAGL-X

Scenario1 : Given I am logged on as a farmer/agent to BISS (pre-submit)
And if I have any Red notifications from AMS
And I see panel
With header AMS findings
And underneath I see AMS status
And I see a red triangle symbol showing my Red notifications, with the label “AMS findings”
And I see a label marked Response required with a red symbol to the right
And I see Amount and the number of red notifications I have
And I see Respond to findings button (green)
And when I press it it will take me to the AMS screen
And I will see a message in this panel –" You have until 8 July 2026 to respond to your AMS notifications"

Scenario2: Given I am logged on as a farmer/agent to BISS
And if I dont have any Red notifications from AMS
I will not see the AMS findings panel displayed on the Farmer Dashboard

Scenario3 : Given I am logged on as a farmer in a partnership and I am the primary partner
And if I have any Red notifications from AMS
And I see panel
With header AMS findings
And underneath I see AMS status
And I see a red triangle symbol showing my Red notifications, with the label “AMS findings”
And I see a label marked Response required with a red symbol to the right
And I see Amount and the number of red notifications I have
And I see Respond to findings button (green)
And when I press it it will take me to the AMS screen
And I will see a message in this panel –" You have until 8 July 2026 to respond to your AMS notifications"

Scenario4 : Given I am logged on as a farmer in a partnership and I am not the primary partner
And if I have any Red notifications from AMS
And I see panel
With header AMS (Area Monitoring System) findings
And underneath I see AMS status
And I see a red triangle symbol showing my Red notifications, with the label “AMS findings”
And I see a label marked Response required with a red symbol to the right
And I see Amount and the number of red notifications I have
And I dont see the Respond to findings button (green)
Then I will see a message in this panel –"The Primary Partner has until 8 July 2026 to respond to your AMS notifications"
